[{"id":"VR615329","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. The figure on the left is labeled Situation 1: No Acceleration, and it shows a block attached to the bottom end of a vertical rope that is suspended from a ceiling. There are two points on the rope, labeled A and B from bottom to top. The figure on the right is labeled Situation 2: Acceleration to the Right, and it shows a block moving to the right on a horizontal surface. A horizontal rope is attached to the right side of the block. There are two points on the rope, labeled A and B from left to right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615329.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A uniform rope with nonnegligible mass is attached to a block in two different situations, as shown in the figures. In Situation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the block is suspended from the ceiling and remains motionless. In Situation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the rope can be modeled as completely horizontal. In which situation, if either, does the magnitude of the tension at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> equal the magnitude of the tension at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR615329_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Situation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Situation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Both situations</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Neither situation</p>"],"answer":3}]